{"interaction":{"author":{"id":13286630,"link":"http://gravatar.com/ding1971","username":"ding1971"},"content":"<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/irish-citizens-abroad-dealing-active-shooter-patrick-finucane\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-183\"><img class=\"alignright size-large wp-image-183\" src=\"https://somniumquecavere.files.wordpress.com/2015/11/screen-shot-2015-11-25-at-15-15-38.png?w=680\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-11-25 at 15.15.38\" width=\"680\" height=\"494\" /></a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">For the greater part of thirty years the Northern Ireland troubles were the main focus of the security services in Ireland, and it was this realisation that was reflected in government policy on both sides of the border. <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>Today, the situation is different, the threat posed from Islamic extremism is far more fluid and harder to detect.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>As can be seen from the recent events in Mali and in Paris, it is a much more violent, immediate and damaging process.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>Contrary to popular belief it is not indiscriminate in nature - it is specific and targeted. Neither economic nor social exclusion are the sole motivating factors which lead individuals to engage in terrorist activities. But despite the fact that different groups or individuals may carry out an attack they all share similarities; </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">a) they usually consist of multiple co-ordinated attacks against high profile iconic targets or locations, typically they are symbols of Western consumerism or critical infrastructure points, b) there is always a desire for high media impact and quite often such attacks take place with a combined PR strategy through Social Media applications, and finally the main emphasis is to overwhelm the target audience with<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>mass casualties. The willingness to create mass casualties is key for many of those involved, it is through such tactics that groups such as ISIS, Al Qaeda and Al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb focus media attention to their respective causes.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>Despite the stated Irish position of neutrality, Irish citizens have been involved in, and in some instances lost their lives in events in Bali, Westgate, 7/7 bombings and in Paris.?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The Department of Foreign Affairs deliver travel advisory notices to Irish citizens travelling abroad through their website and dedicated Twitter feed, but the difficulty with this service is that often it is reactive and not timely.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>In the case of travelling through Western Africa for instance, there is limited assistance available to Irish citizens, and it is in such locations that groups such as Boko Haram, Al Shabab and<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>Al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb prosper.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>The main threat to Irish citizens in these regions is initially that of kidnap.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>There are several documented cases of Western citizens being kidnapped and held for months before being executed by their captors.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>In keeping with the UK and France, Ireland does not have an official policy of paying ransoms. But for those who do have to travel to a volatile region there are some precautions that can be taken prior to travelling - registration with either the DFA or the FCO (in the case of UK nationals), ensuring that you are up to date with regional events and where possible participation on a hostile environment training programme with an accredited institution (HEST training). None will guarantee your safety, but they will increase your chances of survival in a<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>developing scenario.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>Typically terrorist actions in Europe and Western Africa are accurately described as ?active shooter? scenarios - essentially they involve the presence of a highly mobile terrorist units (or individuals) who are actively engaged in tracking down targets for assassination as was the case in Paris, Mali and the Westgate siege in Kenya in 2013.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>During the Westgate attack it was the presence of a former Irish Army Special Forces operator working in Kenya who was accredited with<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>aggressively engaging Al Shabab terrorists during the siege,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>resulting in the escape of several hostages.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? ?</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">For those already working in high risk environments, it is critical that realistic procedures are put in place to protect vulnerable persons, and while such procedures may never be needed they should form a central part to a corporation or group?s business resilience and continuity plan. The incorporation of dynamic lockdown procedures and situational awareness is a key factor in establishing a safe zone for those caught up in an escalating scenario. <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>For the majority of people travelling abroad it may not be necessary to undergo such rigorous preparations - however common sense should prevail regardless of where you are travelling to.?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\"><b>How to Prepare</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Check local news and websites for updates on the current situation</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Register with DFA/FCO prior to departure</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Where necessary check your insurance covers for travel to conflict regions</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">If you are travelling with work - is there a family liaison officer appointed in the event something goes wrong?</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Charge your mobile device fully and never leave it away from your person</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Consider learning First Aid</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Pack a small First Aid kit </span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Always maintain situational awareness - regardless of the location and company you are with</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">In the event you are involved in an escalating situation, follow the advice of the UK FCO pamphlet and Run, Hide and Tell (<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/478003/NaCTSO_Guidance_Note_1_-_2015_-_Dynamic_Lockdown_v1_0.pdf\"><span class=\"s2\">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/478003/NaCTSO_Guidance_Note_1_-_2015_-_Dynamic_Lockdown_v1_0.pdf</span></a>) </span></li>\r\n</ul>","created_at":"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 15:18:34 +0000","id":"1e59387cafb4a100866be4e7c1e22761","link":"http://somniumquecavere.wordpress.com/2015/11/25/travelling-abroad-dealing-with-an-active-shooter-scenario/","received_at":1448464714.8719001,"schema":{"version":3},"subtype":"post","title":"Travelling abroad - Dealing with an Active Shooter scenario","type":"wordpress","tags":["tab7"]},"language":{"tag":"en","tag_extended":"en","confidence":99},"links":{"code":[200],"created_at":["Wed, 25 Nov 201