resulting in the escape of several hostages.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? ?</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">For those already working in high risk environments, it is critical that realistic procedures are put in place to protect vulnerable persons, and while such procedures may never be needed they should form a central part to a corporation or group?s business resilience and continuity plan. The incorporation of dynamic lockdown procedures and situational awareness is a key factor in establishing a safe zone for those caught up in an escalating scenario. <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">? </span>For the majority of people travelling abroad it may not be necessary to undergo such rigorous preparations - however common sense should prevail regardless of where you are travelling to.?</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s2\"><b>How to Prepare</b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Check local news and websites for updates on the current situation</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Register with DFA/FCO prior to departure</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Where necessary check your insurance covers for travel to conflict regions</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">If you are travelling with work - is there a family liaison officer appointed in the event something goes wrong?</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Charge your mobile device fully and never leave it away from your person</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Consider learning First Aid</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Pack a small First Aid kit </span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Always maintain situational awareness - regardless of the location and company you are with</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">In the event you are involved in an escalating situation, follow the advice of the